Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:56.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So thrilled to see you here, Great Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.17,0:01:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming such a long way to our hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:01.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My, I didn't realize it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.72,0:02:04.68,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Onda Yoshirou (58)\NAoiya Inn Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.51,0:02:05.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Since you did tell me over the phone that\Nthree of you would be coming tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.47,0:02:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I closed my last case quickly and\Nhave arrived earlier than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.94,0:02:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, what about that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the attaché case we talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I haven't looked inside during these five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.07,0:02:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, it has a lock on it, so even if I wanted to...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.62,0:02:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.58,0:02:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll manage something for the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.33,0:02:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.33,0:02:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you open it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.67,0:02:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fear not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall share the truth with you as\Nsoon as I have pierced this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.46,0:02:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me, Mouri Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:48.10,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,MOURI KOGOROU'S IMPOSTER
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:48.10,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(PART ONE)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.23,0:02:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The air is so fresh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Humans are best suited for nature, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:03:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you didn't have to purposely get off the\Ntaxi early just to take a walk in this forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inn we're headed to is at the end of this forest, and\Nwe have plenty of time before our appointment, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.25,0:03:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wanted to get there in advance\Nto hang around and take a bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.50,0:03:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides that, why don't you take off those sunglasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.84,0:03:17.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It gives a bad impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mosquito bite above the eyelid is not something\Nto be seen from the genius Mouri Kogorou!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:27.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, it gives me a cool look if some fan\Ngirls are waiting all excited for me at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.44,0:03:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.56,0:03:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who put this stone here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.86,0:03:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a Jizo statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must've fallen on the ground by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's put it back in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you raise up that Jizo, you'll be cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the famous detective Mouri\NKogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} I almost arrested last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.59,0:04:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the incompetent detective from Gunma Prefecture...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.59,0:04:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing at a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have some business to do at the Aoiya Inn over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.98,0:04:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, could you be referring to the\Nunidentified body with the red jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.11,0:04:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm also heading to the Aoiya Inn for that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.78,0:04:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body was found in this Kashiragami Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\c&H67CCF3&}Kashira{\c&HFBD874&}gami {\c&&HFFFFFF&}is the jinx {\c&HFBD874&}god\N{\c&&HFFFFFF&}responsible for {\c&H67CCF3&}head{\c&&HFFFFFF&}aches.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that when people worrying\Ntheir heads enter this forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll be enchanted by Kashiragami\Nand be unable to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.17,0:04:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, this place is famous for suicides.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Famous for suicides?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:47.59,Dialogue Top,Note,0,0,0,,Maedaore Jizo literally means\NFront Fallen Buddhist Statue
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.13,0:04:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.88,0:04:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The statue you were about to raise is the\N"Maedaore Jizo" that calms the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that, when you raise it up, you also\Nwake the evil spirits that bring disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it's been in this fallen\Nposition since a long while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.64,0:04:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that we're heading to the same\Nplace, why don't you ride in my car?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:05:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, thank you, my daughter said\Nshe wanted to walk in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, your daughter is already inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.28,0:05:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the body was found by an Aoiya Inn employee?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He discovered it while going into the\Nforest to pick up wild vegetables, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something strange about this body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by "strange"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body was carrying a car key,\Nbut there was no driver's license.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also had cigarettes on him,\Nbut no lighters or matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.39,0:05:35.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And despite him having died in\Nsummer, he was wearing a sweater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.14,0:05:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know he died in the summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were some things in the victim's bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a pack of milk and some red bean bread with\Nexpiration dates from exactly four years ago on July 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.37,0:05:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We also found a receipt for those items from a nearby\Nconvenience store in the wallet, so there's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:06:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, due to the shock of the body falling on the ground,\Nthe milk and red bean bread were totally smashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a rope around his neck with the other\Nedge of the rope being tied to a broken branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The branch probably broke after he hung himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.76,0:06:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means it looks exactly like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so I thought I could get information on those\Nstrange points from the employee that found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.02,0:06:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I came out here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what brings you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the owner of the inn said he met\Nwith the man wearing the red jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.58,0:06:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, he said it was around October five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The story went that a man in a red jacket suddenly\Nentered the inn, found the owner, and said to him:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I will give you 100,000 yen if you keep this\Nattaché case and envelope safe for me."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll come retrieve it in one year even if I die!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.77,0:06:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An attaché case and an envelope?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:06:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also said, "Give me back the attaché case if I'm the\None that comes, and the envelope if it's anybody else."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.03,0:07:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we can't say for sure that the man in the red\Njacket is the one whose body was found in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.28,0:07:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that man made it clear by saying, "Don't forget my\Nred jacket and long hair," so they're probably the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems he didn't come\Nback to retrieve it after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, the body\Nis one of a man with long hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.55,0:07:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, maybe it's like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.47,0:07:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man entrusted it to the inn owner five years ago\Nwhile saying, "I'll come retrieve it even if I die."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when he returned one summer later...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was traveling through the\Nforest, he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.10,0:07:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a fool of a man!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.81,0:07:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can't take it back if he's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the inn owner called\Non me to solve the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.61,0:07:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man paid the owner to keep it quiet from the\Npolice, so that's why he stayed mum until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did nobody come to claim that attaché case in the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, a day after the red-jacketed man entrusted it to the\Ninn, another man claiming to be his proxy appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A suspicious guy with a hat, sunglasses and a beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.64,0:08:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner hesitated a little but handed over the\Nenvelope as instructed by the man in the red jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.19,0:08:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.69,0:08:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guy opened the envelope and, upon seeing\Nthe memo inside, tore it apart in anger...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And threw it in the garbage can in the lobby\Nand left the inn, never to be seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was written on this memo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.54,0:08:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inn's owner was also interested in it and tried\Nto put back together the pieces of the torn memo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was able to make out seven characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.13,0:08:52.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if they were written with blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.17,0:08:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I shall kill you with my curse."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.93,0:09:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I told you to not come with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, if we ask the inn's owner to show us what's\Ninside the attaché case, Uncle can solve the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.07,0:09:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that inside that attaché\Ncase is that man's long hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you were too noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.33,0:09:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:30.25,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Jinbo Masao (34)\NAoiya Inn Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.87,0:09:30.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Allow me to park your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.50,0:09:32.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, this is quite a good inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.14,0:09:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it your first time coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.72,0:09:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You told us that you were coming\Nto question an employee again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.56,0:09:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked him to come to the station last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.69,0:09:49.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.36,0:09:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Urakawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.82,0:09:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the employee who found the body, Urakawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:09:59.53,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well, I was really surprised at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:10:05.45,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Urakawa Eiji (37)\NAoiya Inn Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.53,0:10:03.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I couldn't imagine that someone may have died there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:05.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Even though it had turned into bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.87,0:10:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you alone when you found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.37,0:10:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, are you the only one who\Ngoes out for wild vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.17,0:10:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jinbo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, the inn's owner Onda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand I all three alternate with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:25.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm the most prone to finding\Ncorpses among the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.39,0:10:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could tell by the atmosphere that it was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.39,0:10:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I can't help it because it's\Ngenerally my turn after the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We close this inn every year before summer\Nvacation in order to go on a company trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The entrance to the forest is\Njust in front of this inn, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When no one's looking, people with suicidal thoughts\Nlike to grab their chances and come to the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if it's suicide, there's nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:11:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man with the sunglasses,\Nisn't he a police officer too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Feared by all with something to hide, the Great Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:08.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.89,0:11:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the companion of Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.31,0:11:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it—he's actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's about Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he's already waiting in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.49,0:11:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.91,0:11:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogorou is already at this inn!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he came three hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the attaché case is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.33,0:11:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took it to his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.37,0:11:38.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's very nice and gave his autograph to every employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.96,0:11:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't soil it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will place it in a frame and put it on display later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.81,0:11:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is this man now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.93,0:11:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Room number 209.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to scold him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.52,0:11:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.48,0:11:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten these kinds of\Nscenes from historical dramas?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.69,0:12:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are lots of tasty scenes when the\Nimposter and true person come face to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Enduring the unendurable and tolerating the intolerable...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall wait until this guy begins\Nhis absurd deduction show...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.00,0:12:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then appear and reveal my great deduction\Nto an extent that will floor absolutely everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.04,0:12:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this crazy talk now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yamamura, please talk some sense into him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please make me a part of this plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.06,0:12:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, may I please have your names?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.56,0:12:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our names?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Echigo Mitsuemon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.73,0:12:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let us say that this one is a plain, humble man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Touché, samurai!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I care not if my room is the cheapest one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir, it seems that the young lady\Nforgot her cell phone in your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your daughter's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.76,0:13:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thy kindness is appreciated!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.88,0:13:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thou shalt be blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.59,0:13:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We shall now take our leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:12.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O my dear assistant, let us indulge\Nin a hot bath and some drinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nay, good sir, on duty I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.31,0:13:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he calls himself Echigo Mitsuemon...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.25,0:13:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great going!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep it up and deal with the imposter so that\NI can enjoy your deduction show tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.00,0:13:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just leave that to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.10,0:13:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy hasn't started his deduction show yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.06,0:13:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I told you we should've scolded him before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.02,0:13:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This fake may have already fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it seems nobody left the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.57,0:14:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped—how about\NI give him a little piece of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.11,0:14:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you there, imposter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.16,0:14:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this, it's all dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.67,0:14:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's sleeping in a sulk because\Nhe couldn't solve the mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.00,0:14:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn you, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, Mouri Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.30,0:14:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.22,0:14:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.52,0:14:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.61,0:14:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.61,0:14:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Mouri just hanged himself in his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.58,0:14:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, hurry up, officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.63,0:15:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what an unbearable sight you've become...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't very well see your face because of all my tears!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did you do such a foolish thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that the Sleeping\NKogorou will sleep for eternity...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.35,0:15:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is too much for a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.35,0:15:18.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you grumbling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hadn't let anyone else enter the scene, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.15,0:15:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd better hurry and call your fellow\NGunma prefecture police and forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.99,0:15:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An imposter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.12,0:15:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.66,0:15:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that man is just a fake who\Nborrowed Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is the one and only, the\Nfamous detective Mouri Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.54,0:15:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, I was sure I'd already\Nseen your face somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My deepest apologies, I'd never seen your face before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.80,0:15:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did this person impersonate you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he wanted to see what\Nwas inside this attaché case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, the key is still in the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.11,0:16:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's have a look inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.74,0:16:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sports newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akagimaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.33,0:16:25.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't this Akagimaru seriously injure himself\Nfour yours ago and have to retire from sumo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look carefully: this newspaper is dated\Nin the September of five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.38,0:16:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, he was rejoiced by fans for his\Nfirst championship in eighteen years at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why was it inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something coming from\Nthe bottom of the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.81,0:16:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, something like black strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, it's just black hair tucked between the pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.61,0:16:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't this hair a little bit long?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:17:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that this is the curse of the long-haired\Nman with the red jacket who died four years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.87,0:17:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If people can get killed by curses, police\Nofficers and detectives may as well retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it probably went like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two men made a bet five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.51,0:17:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were betting on a sports athlete\Nand had to guess his status next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These two men are the man we found\Nwith the long hair and the red jacket...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.81,0:17:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the mustached man who usurped\Nmy name and hanged himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, their target athlete was Akagimaru, who\Nwas in promising condition five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.53,0:17:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man with the long hair told\Nthe mustached man the following:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I've put my answer inside."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm giving this to the inn's owner and the key to\Nyou, so let's check it one year later together."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.96,0:17:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, who's the man that claimed to\Nbe the long-haired man's proxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.26,0:17:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man with the hat and beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was likely the mustached man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the torn memo that had\N"I shall kill you with my curse" on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was meant to be a threat as in, "If you\Ncheat by coming in advance, I'll kill you."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.73,0:18:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But inside the attaché case was only a sports\Nnewspaper, so where is the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:17.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was something else inside—the hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.07,0:18:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When a sumo wrestler cuts his hair, it means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, retirement!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before Akagimaru seriously injured\Nhimself, he won a championship in Nagoya...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.50,0:18:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And got promoted to the rank of Oozeki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.88,0:18:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, they surely bet a large amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The long-haired man who thought\Nthe wrestler would retire...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.55,0:18:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Committed suicide as he was headed\Nto this inn through the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.81,0:18:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did the other one commit suicide too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.23,0:18:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the long-haired man's\Nprediction turned out to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After learning the long-haired\Nman had died four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.82,0:18:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to find out the contents of\Nthe attaché case to conclude the bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He happened to hear that the inn's owner\Nasked me to take on this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.41,0:19:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then impersonated me and was able to\Nconfirm what was inside the attaché case, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.58,0:19:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man's prediction had hit the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he felt guilty for driving the long-haired man to\Nsuicide by demanding a pay-up four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.46,0:19:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And tied his belt around his neck,\Nending his own life as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A great deduction beyond all expectations!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.22,0:19:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, just doing what I do best!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.02,0:19:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're definitely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:36.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for it to be a curse\Nin this scientific era we're living in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.48,0:19:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.90,0:19:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These strings of hair have different lengths, and\Nthere's some permed hair and brown hair too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.37,0:19:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beyond that, it also feels a little bit wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.37,0:19:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think hair that's been\Nwet for five years is cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not the long-haired man's curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.30,0:20:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the grudge of a hippie guy\Nwith long, brown hair and a perm!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.43,0:20:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, now that I think of it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}'s\Nhair was also wet a few minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course, I was taking a bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.81,0:20:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, don't say strange things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.85,0:20:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.48,0:20:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you told us that you couldn't enter the bath last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.24,0:20:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time there was a "cleaning" sign on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of being wet, the tatami at the entrance\Nto this room was also wet when we came.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.62,0:20:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you clean the bathroom every evening in this inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the bath cleaning is supposed to be during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.30,0:20:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means someone from this inn put a "cleaning"\Nsign on the women's bath in order to keep people out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They also took a load of long hair from the\Ndrain there and brought it back to this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.89,0:21:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, they inserted the hair in the attaché case's sports\Nnewspaper to mimic the long-haired man's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.32,0:21:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible they did this in order\Nto disturb the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, don't tell me this is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.87,0:21:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, the reason the tatami is wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.96,0:21:18.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Revolves around the culprit hurrying\Nto the bath with their socks on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.17,0:21:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they returned to this\Nroom, their feet remained wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.75,0:21:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.51,0:21:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our culprit who knew where the "cleaning" sign was\Nstored is likely to be among the inn employees!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.27,0:21:45.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is likely someone linked to the long-\Nhaired man who committed suicide four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.53,0:21:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's bugging me is the strangeness of this body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.12,0:21:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had car keys on him but no driver's license...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.79,0:21:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he had cigarettes but without a lighter or matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:22:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, he was wearing a sweater in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.50,0:22:05.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, this long-haired man didn't commit\Nsuicide either, but was also murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.93,0:22:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody did something to\Nthis body to achieve their goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:23.19,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,MOURI KOGOROU'S IMPOSTER
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:23.19,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.57,0:22:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, don't tell me this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.19,0:22:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.15,0:22:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, our culprit who knew where the "cleaning" sign\Nwas stored is likely to be among the inn employees!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.29,0:22:40.75,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\move(451.205,335,737.653,335)}Jinbo Masao (34)\NAoiya Inn Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.29,0:22:40.75,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\move(186.792,335,472.238,335)}Onda Yoshirou (58)\NAoiya Inn Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.29,0:22:40.75,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\move(-71.534,335,214.936,335)}Urakawa Eiji (37)\NAoiya Inn Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.13,0:22:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is likely someone linked to the long-\Nhaired man who committed suicide four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.59,0:22:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, this long-haired man didn't commit\Nsuicide either, but was also murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.59,0:22:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody did something to this\Nbody to achieve their goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.97,0:22:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who did it, and what for?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.27,0:23:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I found a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.57,0:23:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was in this coat that belonged to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.95,0:23:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one number in its memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.70,0:23:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we try to call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.07,0:23:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.34,0:23:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Tatsuo?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.17,0:23:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened with that get rich\Nquick scheme you told me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me know if it went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.13,0:23:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.51,0:23:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a call from your apartment's landlord.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:39.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Said something like, "If you don't pay your rent,\NI won't renew your contract and will kick you out."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.73,0:23:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you listening, Tatsuo?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.19,0:23:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.44,0:23:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I have a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.77,0:23:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call me back later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.69,0:23:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.99,0:23:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He mentioned a "get rich quick" scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.16,0:23:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also that if he doesn't pay his\Nrent, his contract won't be renewed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.70,0:23:57.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renew?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.45,0:24:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now that we know that the victim's name\Nis Mori Tatsuo, we're making progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.71,0:24:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know his surname is "Mori"?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.96,0:24:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He only mentioned "Tatsuo".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, there is a sticker with his name on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.55,0:24:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not a kid, why would he need a sticker?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.18,0:24:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to be a kid, but I also have a sticker on my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.52,0:24:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're still a kid, so that's understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.81,0:24:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, is the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.98,0:24:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mr. Officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.78,0:24:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you give me more details on the\Nlong-haired man's belongings?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.87,0:24:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.87,0:24:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had milk, red bean bread, and\Na receipt on him four years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.50,0:24:42.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.00,0:24:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about you take a look at the pictures if you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.12,0:24:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.21,0:24:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I came to this inn to ask questions\Nabout that, I brought them with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.80,0:24:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the crushed carton of milk, the front and the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.63,0:24:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the crushed red bean\Nbread and a pack of cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.97,0:25:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, the convenience store's\Nreceipt that was in the wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.72,0:25:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The receipt is from July 10th, which is when\Nyou were on your company trip, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.36,0:25:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.23,0:25:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.36,0:25:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finally understand the culprit's objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.70,0:25:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mr. Officer...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.49,0:25:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.74,0:25:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there another body found in Kashiragami Forest\Nat the end of the company's trip four years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.71,0:25:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, one was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.79,0:25:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was near the Maedaore Jizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.29,0:25:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the person who discovered it...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.72,0:25:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.84,0:25:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, that person is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.85,0:25:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this sports newspaper is likely\Na map pointing to a hidden place.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.69,0:25:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I need now is the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.98,0:25:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my deductions are correct, it may still be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.90,0:25:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that shogi board and this desk,\Nthere should be the culprit's prints...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.00,0:26:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.04,0:26:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.96,0:26:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just come in as you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.17,0:26:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was asked by Uncle Kogorou to take a\Ngood look at this shogi board and desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.34,0:26:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By Detective Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.14,0:26:24.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also asked me to look at the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.93,0:26:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Light?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.18,0:26:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said it might be the clinching\Nmove to corner the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.07,0:26:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, according to the estimated time of death, the\Ncrime happened today between 4:00 and 5:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.16,0:26:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, the culprit put up the "cleaning'' sign...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.74,0:26:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gathered long hair from the bath, and\Nbrought it back to the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.16,0:26:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They tried to interfere with the investigation by\Nmaking it look like the long-haired man's curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.84,0:27:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we suppose that only the employees of this inn\Nknow where the "cleaning" sign is stored...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.13,0:27:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can narrow down our list of suspects!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.80,0:27:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please gather all the employees as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.60,0:27:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need to inquire as to their where-\Nabouts this evening one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.02,0:27:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second, officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.19,0:27:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't the employees who never heard about or\Nnever saw the man who died four years ago be cleared?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.41,0:27:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you were all here when this man gave the attaché\Ncase to Onda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} five years ago, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.12,0:27:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he handed it to me in the\Nroom he was staying in, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.17,0:27:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hired this guy here four years ago in the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.00,0:27:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, I only told my employees I called Detective Mouri\Nto investigate the attaché case we'd kept for five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.22,0:27:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never told them it belonged to that long-haired man.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.93,0:27:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.68,0:27:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the only one who knew about both the\Nattaché case and the long-haired man...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.56,0:27:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is you, the owner, and no one else, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.69,0:28:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.49,0:28:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I were the culprit, I would've opened\Nit without safekeeping it for five years!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.24,0:28:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And don't you find it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.70,0:28:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That such an important case would only\Ncontain an old sports newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.62,0:28:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet the culprit already stole something wrapped\Nin the newspaper and fled somewhere far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.38,0:28:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've changed the circumstances if the\Nnewspaper contained a special meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.97,0:28:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.72,0:28:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.18,0:28:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this "Mae 5"?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.39,0:28:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, next to the winner Akagimaru's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.90,0:28:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mae 5" is written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.15,0:28:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means number five in the Maegashira rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.48,0:28:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, Akagimaru was in the East corner,\Nmeaning he was an East Maegashira Number 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.24,0:28:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maegashira?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.87,0:28:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it somehow related to Kashiragami Forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.95,0:28:52.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, no way they're related.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.33,0:28:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about Maedaore Jizo?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.33,0:28:56.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.75,0:29:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maegashira is the rank below Yokozuna, Oozeki,\NSekiwake and Komusubi in the top sumo divisions...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.88,0:29:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "number five" means he placed fifth in that rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.18,0:29:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Akagimaru wasn't that strong\Nbut still won the tournament...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.06,0:29:16.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've been very careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.27,0:29:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Careful?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.11,0:29:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because look here, Akagimaru only fell into a hole once!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.70,0:29:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't this black circle mean that a\Nsumo wrestler fell into a trap hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.95,0:29:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's "thrust down" written under the black circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not a hole, but a symbol for "black star".
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.75,0:29:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means Akagimaru lost the bout\Non the eighth day by that move.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.75,0:29:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so it wasn't that he walked\Neight steps and fell in a hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.01,0:29:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, gather your employees and\Ncooperate as I carry out the questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.30,0:29:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, everyone will be\Nquestioned without exception!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.39,0:30:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there was nobody that can confirm\Nyour actions this evening, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.19,0:30:02.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.53,0:30:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.82,0:30:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next person!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.82,0:30:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on a minute, is this going to take long?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.03,0:30:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to clean the cafeteria...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.87,0:30:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I have to prepare tomorrow's breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.29,0:30:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you let us leave earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.00,0:30:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.25,0:30:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like I've got everyone down for now...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.92,0:30:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there are almost none of you with\Na solid alibi between 4:00 to 5:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.30,0:30:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That much is obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.85,0:30:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My employees are constantly on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.43,0:30:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I haven't hired any strange person that'd\Nobserve everyone while looking at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.56,0:30:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess so...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.31,0:30:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.40,0:30:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.07,0:30:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.53,0:30:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Yamamura speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.62,0:30:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.16,0:30:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.41,0:30:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.75,0:31:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.96,0:31:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, what did my father say?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.05,0:31:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.05,0:31:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As he was gathering information from\Nthe people living around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.34,0:31:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was mistaken for a suspicious person by\Nan officer and is now at the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.14,0:31:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.60,0:31:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, I'm going to that station to free them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.27,0:31:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.07,0:31:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.82,0:31:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You and your employees can take a rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.53,0:31:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be conducting a thorough\Nquestioning at a later time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.62,0:31:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.24,0:32:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stones?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.57,0:32:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.99,0:32:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.58,0:33:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you looking for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.66,0:33:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jinbo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.79,0:33:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or would you prefer...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.67,0:33:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called you what you really are: the culprit behind\Nthe 100 million yen blackmail case?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.59,0:33:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.96,0:33:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out everything when I checked the\Nserial numbers on this 100 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.64,0:33:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, two men threatened a\Nconfectionery company and stole 100 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.39,0:33:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are one of those two men.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.90,0:33:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the other one is the long-haired man who\Nentrusted the attaché case to the inn's owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.57,0:33:38.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sports newspaper inside indicates the\Nplace where the stolen money was hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.16,0:33:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akagimaru, who is shown in the newspaper\Nheading, was an East Maegashira-5 at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.20,0:33:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maegashira is a keyword pointing to the\NMaedaore Jizo here in Kashiragami Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.09,0:33:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that, starting from the fallen\Nstatue, you walk five steps east.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.22,0:34:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, in accordance with Akagimaru's record chart,\Nyou turn right and advance another eight steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.72,0:34:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you dig a hole on that point, you\Nwill find the urn with all the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.65,0:34:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.44,0:34:18.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why the long-haired man entrusted the\Nattaché case with the newspaper to the inn's owner...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.11,0:34:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because he sensed something was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.66,0:34:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sensed that you wanted to kill him\Nin order to keep all the money yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.71,0:34:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the long-haired man could've\Neasily guessed your intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.00,0:34:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that the long-haired man was\Nlikely the one who carried the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.05,0:34:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And yet you decided that he should meet\Nyou in this forest that's famous for suicides.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.60,0:34:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof, the long-haired man also\Nentrusted the memo with the attaché case.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.10,0:34:53.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In case you killed him and came alone to\Nretrieve it, he could deliver the vile message.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.73,0:34:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected, you killed him in this\Nforest and made it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.95,0:35:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you rushed all exultant to the inn...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.70,0:35:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With your face hidden with a hat,\Na pair of glasses, and a beard.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.91,0:35:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the only thing you found was the\Nmemo with "I shall kill you with my curse".
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.83,0:35:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because you couldn't give up on the money, you\Ndecided to get employed and search the inn's vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.80,0:35:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Days and months passed, and the\Nlong-haired man's corpse was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.30,0:35:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you heard the inn's owner decided to call me in to\Ninvestigate the attaché case he was given five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.27,0:35:33.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You quickly hired someone to impersonate me...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.52,0:35:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And had him retrieve the attaché case before\NI came in order to obtain the contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.57,0:35:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was no money inside,\Nonly an old sports newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.58,0:35:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The imposter who was promised a\Nbig compensation became upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.91,0:35:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably said, "If I don't get the money, I'll tell\Neverything to the real Mouri Kogorou that's on his way."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.50,0:36:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With no other choice, you killed the man\Nand decided to let me handle the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.22,0:36:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, the fact you came here to search\Nfor the money is the definitive proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.10,0:36:11.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, come to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.77,0:36:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.61,0:36:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here merely because an inspiration\Nhit me when I saw the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.03,0:36:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I could help with\Nthe investigation by searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.61,0:36:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.53,0:36:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also, the long-haired man\Ndied four years ago on July 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.70,0:36:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on the company retreat that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.25,0:36:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the long-haired man wasn't killed\Nduring the summer four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was five years ago in autumn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.13,0:36:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just after he entrusted the attaché case to the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.18,0:36:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put the milk, bread, cigarettes, and convenience\Nstore receipt inside his backpack afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.02,0:36:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did it to manipulate the estimated\Ntime of death and create your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.48,0:37:04.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Items like the milk and receipt belonged to another suicide\Nbody you'd found after the company trip four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.45,0:37:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the long-haired man was wearing a sweater, and\Nhad cigarettes on him despite lacking a lighter or matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.45,0:37:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took away the long-haired man's\Ndriver's license because his was expiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.54,0:37:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had been carrying a driver's license\Nthat hadn't been renewed for a year...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.88,0:37:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The alibi trick would have been exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.76,0:37:26.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition, the reason you inserted\Nstrains of long hair in the newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.26,0:37:32.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to lead us to believe that someone related to\Nthe long-haired man killed the fake Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.81,0:37:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, with the alibi provided by the receipt, you would\Nallow yourself to be removed from the suspect list.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.23,0:37:39.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no one fell for your trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.15,0:37:44.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why not tell me how can you be so sure\Nthat I planted the milk and receipt afterward?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.11,0:37:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't it be that the long-haired man\Nbrought those in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.12,0:37:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.45,0:37:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because of...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.12,0:37:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The straw.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.04,0:37:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no straw on the pack of milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.75,0:38:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is proof that someone refilled a\Ndiscarded milk carton with milk...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.88,0:38:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sealed the opening with glue and\Nput it inside the man's backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.09,0:38:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one in their right mind would put an\Nopened milk carton in their backpack.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.10,0:38:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, that's it, exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.85,0:38:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did you guys see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.90,0:38:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see me murdering this long-haired man?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.73,0:38:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, we were too late to establish that\Nyou were the murderer for that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.16,0:38:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we do possess proof that you\Nkilled the man who impersonated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.00,0:38:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.04,0:38:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To take someone on your shoulder\Nand hang them from a high place...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.08,0:38:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to get them near the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.88,0:38:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To accomplish that, you climbed atop the\Nshogi board and the desk in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.22,0:38:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, you likely removed\Nyour socks in order to not slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.43,0:38:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The forensics officer reported having\Nfound someone's footprints on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.85,0:39:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, what will happen should we\Ncompare those prints with your own feet?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.90,0:39:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, I did climb on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.49,0:39:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was to change the light bulb in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.49,0:39:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.49,0:39:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you check the light, you should find my fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.08,0:39:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was quite surprised that there\Nwere a lot of your fingerprints...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.12,0:39:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all under a thick layer of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.09,0:39:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You likely left those fingerprints quite some time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.01,0:39:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite that, your footprints were still on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.39,0:39:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could only mean you are the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.77,0:39:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, no inn would leave their desks unwiped long\Nenough to have thick dust collected on the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.56,0:39:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jinbo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, knock it off already.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.15,0:39:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no use trying to cheat time.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.99,0:39:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.41,0:39:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you find out I was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.20,0:39:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your actions gave it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.29,0:40:03.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when you came to give back my\Ndaughter's cell phone in the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.17,0:40:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you'd never seen Detective\NYamamura who was next to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.46,0:40:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You gave it to me without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.43,0:40:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying, "It's your daughter's, right?"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.47,0:40:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.06,0:40:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw the sticker saying "Ran\NMouri" on the cell phone, I knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.56,0:40:28.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, you already knew the minute you saw me...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.82,0:40:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I was the genuine Mouri Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.83,0:40:45.21,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,Kuraki Mai
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.09,0:40:52.84,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.38,0:40:55.97,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love to you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.26,0:40:58.10,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.56,0:41:01.22,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,Always give my love to you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.35,0:41:09.40,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,son janai!? ima kara demo\Niin janai!? yareru koto
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.35,0:41:09.40,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,Don't you think so!? From now on, let's... Isn't it great!? Do what we can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.49,0:41:20.08,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,omotta doori ni yatte miyou\Nkimi to deau made
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.49,0:41:20.08,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,With the way I feel now, I know I had nothing before you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.58,0:41:26.75,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,nani mo nakatta keredo me wo tojite omou
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.58,0:41:26.75,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,But when I close my eyes and think...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.88,0:41:31.46,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,issho ni ikiru basho ga aru kara
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.88,0:41:31.46,Dialogue,ED EN,0,0,0,,I know there's a place where we can live together
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.67,0:41:37.97,Dialogue Top,ED JP,0,0,0,,always ai wo mune ni yuuki wo dashite
